<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,636,1139,1165]" box="[189,636,1139,1165]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1139,1165]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Description</emphasis>
(from 
<bibRefCitation author="Levi &amp; Levi" box="[415,628,1139,1165]" firstAuthor="Levi" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="931 - 997" refId="ref23610" refString="Levi C. &amp; Levi P. 1983. Demosponges bathyales recoltees par le N / O ' Vauban' au sud de la Nouvelle- Caledonie. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (4, A) 5 (4): 931 - 997." type="journal article" year="1983">Lévi &amp; Lévi 1983</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1187,1360]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Small grey specimen of 2 × 
<quantity box="[545,617,1187,1213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
encrusting the internal valve of a bivalve mollusk. The surface and interior is clathrate, with cavities of 
<quantity box="[687,810,1224,1250]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2 mm</quantity>
diameter. The skeletal architecture is reticulated and irregularly unispicular. Oxeas are 650–800 × 25–30 μm, flagellosigmas ovoid with upturned long endings and wide-angled short endings, longest axis 125–130 μm, width 70–85 μm, normal sigmas (common) 100–120 × 2–3 μm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,497,1401,1427]" box="[189,497,1401,1427]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,497,1401,1427]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,497,1401,1427]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1334,1449,1475]" box="[189,1334,1449,1475]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<collectingCountry box="[189,374,1449,1475]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[385,518,1449,1475]" degrees="22.5333" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" precision="5" value="-22.5333">22.5333° S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[531,680,1449,1475]" degrees="166.4167" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" precision="5" value="166.4167">166.4167° E</geoCoordinate>
, depth 
<quantity box="[765,898,1449,1475]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="465.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="430.0">430–500 m</quantity>
(Marine Ecoregion 
<collectingCountry box="[1135,1322,1449,1475]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,303,1516,1542]" box="[189,303,1516,1542]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1516,1542]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1516,1542]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1564,1775]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi &amp; Levi" authorityYear="1983" box="[311,423,1566,1591]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Gellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="anatarius">
<emphasis box="[311,423,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">anatarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(‘duck-like’, referring to the upturned long ending) is changed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Levi &amp; Levi" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[1190,1291,1566,1591]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="anataria">
<emphasis box="[1190,1291,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">anataria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to match the female gender of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1841" box="[435,552,1601,1627]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[435,552,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Haliclona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Due to the large oxeas and sigmas this species can clearly be associated with the known species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[511,765,1638,1664]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
<emphasis box="[511,628,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[647,755,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Flagellia</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[774,923,1638,1664]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The flagellosigmas are similar in shape to those of species from nearby 
<collectingCountry box="[589,703,1674,1700]" name="Indonesia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[724,745,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[764,947,1674,1701]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="indonesiae" status="subgen. et sp. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[774,792,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[820,947,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">indonesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[959,1191,1674,1700]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">subgen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[1207,1228,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Thiele" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1247,1391,1674,1701]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hamata" subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[1257,1275,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1303,1391,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[189,210,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[229,404,1711,1738]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hentscheli" subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[239,257,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[285,404,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">hentscheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgen. et nom. nov.), of the 
<collectingCountry box="[783,908,1711,1737]" name="Seychelles" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
species 
<emphasis box="[1016,1037,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[1056,1264,1711,1738]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="amirantensis" status="subgen. et sp. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[1066,1084,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1112,1264,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">amirantensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">subgen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and to a lesser extent of the Guyanan 
<emphasis box="[735,756,1750,1775]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[771,898,1748,1775]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hajdui" status="subgen. et sp. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[781,799,1750,1775]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[823,898,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">hajdui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[906,1122,1748,1774]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">subgen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1815,2025]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<bibRefCitation author="Levi" box="[189,329,1815,1841]" firstAuthor="Levi" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="9 - 87" refId="ref23544" refString="Levi C. 1993. Porifera Demospongiae: Spongiaires bathyaux de Nouvelle-Caledonie, recoltes par le ' Jean Charcot'. Campagne BIOCAL, 1985. In: Crosnier A. (ed.) Resultats des campagnes MUSORSTOM, Volume 11: 9 - 87. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (A, Zoologie) 158, Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris." type="journal article" year="1993">Lévi (1993)</bibRefCitation>
provided an additional 
<collectingCountry box="[607,788,1815,1841]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
deep-water (
<quantity box="[941,1018,1815,1841]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
) record of material belonging to 
<taxonomicName authority="Van Soest, 2017" authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,441,1852,1878]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Flagellia">
<emphasis box="[189,306,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[324,432,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Flagellia</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[449,597,1852,1878]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(reported as a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ridley &amp; Dendy" authorityYear="1886" box="[773,980,1852,1878]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Gellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="flagellifer">
<emphasis box="[773,980,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Gellius flagellifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which is definitely not assignable to 
<emphasis box="[222,243,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Levi &amp; Levi" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[261,418,1889,1915]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="anataria" subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[271,289,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[317,418,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">anataria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it has oxeas of 300–350 × 10 μm, flagellosigmas with straight long endings, 70–105 μm, and two size categories of sigmas, 25–35 and 40–55 μm. Further study is necessary to determine whether it belongs to 
<emphasis box="[561,582,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Van Soest" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[595,774,1962,1989]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Sigmadocia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="flagellifera" subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[605,623,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[646,774,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">flagellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or perhaps to one of the above described species, e.g., 
<emphasis box="[189,210,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Soest" authorityYear="2017" box="[225,396,1999,2025]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hentscheli" subGenus="Flagellia">
(
<emphasis box="[235,253,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">F</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[277,396,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">hentscheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgen. et nom. nov.
</paragraph>
